Since you are asserting that remoteUser must be present you can make unpackPropertiesNoThrow to do that instead.

Simply do: boll remoteUser = false;

Then unpackPropertiesNoThrow will return false if this property is missing. Proper information will be logged by UnpackErrorPrinter.

userPrivileges information is overwritten and setting only to configureSelf. So I was asking for clarification on that change. But i did deep look at code and found answer ( As this is overwritten only when isConfigureSelfOnly is set and for changing the expired passwords). Please ignore the comment. 

userPrivileges = userPrivileges.intersection(
                redfish::Privileges{"ConfigureSelf"});

nit: unpackPropertiesNoThrow has option to validate presence of mandatory properties. Then you could remove this check.

```
        const std::string* userRolePtr = nullptr;
        bool remoteUser = false;
        const bool* passwordExpired = nullptr;

        const bool success = sdbusplus::unpackPropertiesNoThrow(
            redfish::dbus_utils::UnpackErrorPrinter(), userInfoMap,
            "UserPrivilege", userRolePtr, "RemoteUser", remoteUser,
            "UserPasswordExpired", passwordExpired);
```

it will return false and UnpackErrorPrinter will print proper error information when "RemoteUser" is missing or of course it has wrong type
